newsitem.title: DENMARK: Jyske Bank nine-month 96 profit climbs.
newsitem.headline: Jyske Bank nine-month 96 profit climbs.

text.p: Net interest and fees income 1.651 bln vs 1.666 bln Securities and forex results 287 vs 350
Losses and bad debt provisions 180 vs 240
Solvency ratio end-Sept'96 (percent) 11.1 vs 11.0 end-Sept'95 Balance end-Sept'96 55.330 bln vs 48.691 bln end-Sept'95

NOTE - Full name of fourth biggest Danish bank group is Jyske Bank A/S. It said in a statement that it maintained its earlier forecast of full year 1996 profit in the 650-750 million crown range before tax, extraordinary items and securities and currency adjustments.
The result was above average analyst expectations of a pre-tax and extraordinary items profit of 795 million crowns for the period. --Chris Follett, Copenhagen newsroom, +45-33969652
